{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17511532","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17511532"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T12:42:55+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T12:42:55+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11750"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"11750","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/11750"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.23,0.04,0.04,0.08,0.61]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4363"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108502"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"4363","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4363"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11750"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90889"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"34"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"380"},{"type":"tags","id":"2560"},{"type":"tags","id":"2778"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4974"},{"type":"tags","id":"4975"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11633"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"6029"},{"type":"contributions","id":"7678"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26955"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27113"},{"type":"contributions","id":"36498"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40495"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42657"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43267"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108502","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/108502"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 64-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with a one-year history of increasing numbness and tingling in the thumb, index, and long fingers of the left hand. The symptoms are worse at night and also during the day when he is driving his car. He has no significant medical history and does not take any regular medications. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears well with vital signs within normal limits. There is profound grip and pinch weakness and loss of sensation in the affected fingers. An ultrasound is conducted to confirm the diagnosis.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate plan of management for this patient?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Wrist splinting","Oral corticosteroids","Non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs","Physiotherapy","Surgical decompression"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with symptoms and examination findings consistent with carpal tunnel syndrome.  This is caused by compression of the median nerve at the wrist and typically present with numbness and tingling in the thumb, index, and long fingers, often worsening at night or with activities that involve wrist flexion or extension. In most instances treatment should focus on non-surgical interventions, however surgery would be considered in severe cases or where there has been a failure of conservative treatments. Severe cases include those where there is hand numbness, muscle atrophy (such as in this case) or reduced hand activity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWrist splinting\u003C/strong\u003E is generally the most appropriate initial management for carpal tunnel syndrome in uncomplicated and non-severe cases. Splinting the wrist in a neutral position, especially at night, can help reducing pressure on the median nerve which thus reduces symptoms. Patients must also look at the trigger for carpal tunnel syndrome - such as repetitive arm movements for work to prevent ongoing aggravation to the nerve. This would not be appropriate for this patient in which clear muscle atrophy is seen thus making it a severe case. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOral corticosteroids\u003C/strong\u003E may be considered in cases where splinting is ineffective, but they are not typically the first-line treatment due to potential side effects.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESurgical decompression\u003C/strong\u003E is reserved for severe cases or when conservative measures fail such as in this case. This is releasing the transverse carpal ligament to relieve pressure on the median nerve. For this patient, there is atrophy of the musculature in the thenar eminence and it would be appropriate to offer the patient surgical decompression at this stage without first trialing conservative measures which are unlikely to be of assistance. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPhysiotherapy\u003C/strong\u003E can be beneficial as an adjunct to other treatments, but it is not the primary initial management strategy for carpal tunnel syndrome.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENon-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs\u003C/strong\u003E may provide temporary relief of symptoms but do not address the underlying cause of nerve compression and are not considered a primary treatment nor would be sufficient in this case.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Median nerve compression at the level of the carpal tunnel is a common condition.","Carpal tunnel syndrome is characterised by tingling and numbness in the thumb, index, and long fingers.","Initial management of carpal tunnel syndrome often involves conservative measures such as wrist splinting."],"references":["Duvuru G, Stone JH, Imboden JB, Hellmann DB. Current diagnosis and treatment. Rheumatology. [Internet]. Accessed on 13 Jan 2025. Available from: https://accessmedicine.mhmedical.com/content.aspx?bookid=506\u0026sectionid=42584881","Sevy JO, Sina RE, Varacallo MA. Carpal Tunnel Syndrome. [Updated 2023 Oct 29]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2025 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK448179/","Wipperman J, Goerl K. Carpal Tunnel Syndrome: Diagnosis and Management. Am Fam Physician. 2016 Dec 15;94(12):993-999. PMID: 28075090. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/28075090/","Carlson H, Colbert A, Frydl J, Arnall E, Elliot M, Carlson N. Current options for nonsurgical management of carpal tunnel syndrome. Int J Clin Rheumtol. 2010 Feb;5(1):129-142. doi: 10.2217/IJR.09.63. PMID: 20490348; PMCID: PMC2871765. Available from: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC2871765/","Padua L, Coraci D, Erra C, et al. Carpal tunnel syndrome: clinical features, diagnosis, and management Lancet Neurol. 2016; 12:1273-284","Alrayes MS, Altawili M, Alsaffar MH, et al. Surgical Interventions for the Management of Carpal Tunnel Syndrome: A Narrative Review. Cureus 16(3): e55593. DOI 10.7759/cureus.55593"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90889"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11750"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"18484"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"18484","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/18484"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/e79fe985-f682-4bae-9a28-a74931aa6c05.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/e79fe985-f682-4bae-9a28-a74931aa6c05.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":800,"height":540}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90889","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/90889"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-07-11T18:43:21+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-07-11T18:45:06+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4363"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108502"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"7","link